</p></li></ul></section><section id="GUID-1156E15C-FA11-42F7-80CE-F9823F371FA9" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Function</title><p class="- topic/p ">Test the M&amp;C scanner. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">Use a smooth, white opaque, media on roll 1. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">Switch winding off before starting this test. Set the output configuration to: 
<b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Wind the output = NO.</b> 
</p></section><section id="GUID-9B99E924-CF70-4B47-86EB-D79AAE5B3D5F" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Values</title><ul class="- topic/ul "><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Scanner test passed 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Scanner test failed (measurements out of spec) 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Scanner test failed (measurement failed) 
</p></li></ul><p class="- topic/p "><?xm-replace_text Paragraph?>
</p><p class="- topic/p ">The test must have ended successfully. 
</p><p class="- topic/p "> If the scanner test fails, check if the media thickness is correctly set. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">See 
<xref keyref="12adju002" class="- topic/xref " href="GUID-E9976EFB-9920-4523-8E63-376189B17D02.xml" format="dita" locktitle="yes" type="task"><?ditaot usertext?><?xm-replace_text xref?>12 How to measure the media thickness</xref> 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">If so, replace the M&amp;C scanner. 
